############################################################ # Section ############################################################ Section::Begin("");
BEGIN_PGML [`\frac{4}{9}x-\frac{7}{10}y+\frac{2}{3}x`]
[@KeyboardInstructions('If the expression cannot be simplified further, just enter it as it is.')@]**
[_]{$ans[1]}{25}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION This expression has two like terms that can be combined: [`\frac{4}{9}x`] and [`\frac{2}{3}x\text{.}`] To combine them, we need to add the fractions [`\frac{4}{9}+\frac{2}{3}\text{.}`]
[```\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \frac{4}{9}+\frac{2}{3}\amp=\frac{4}{9}+\frac{6}{9}\\ \amp=\frac{10}{9} \end{aligned} ```]
So [`\frac{4}{9}x+\frac{2}{3}x=\frac{10}{9}x\text{.}`] And together with the third term, the answer is [`\frac{10}{9}x-\frac{7}{10}y\text{.}`]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
Section::End();
############################################################ # Section ############################################################ Section::Begin("");
BEGIN_PGML [`\frac{5}{6}y-\frac{8}{15}y+\frac{2}{3}y^2`]
[@KeyboardInstructions('If the expression cannot be simplified further, just enter it as it is.')@]**
[_]{$ans[2]}{25}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION In this expression we can combine the [`y`]-terms. We need to subtract the fractions [`\frac{5}{6}-\frac{8}{15}\text{.}`]
[```\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \frac{5}{6}-\frac{8}{15}\amp=\frac{25}{30}-\frac{16}{30}\\ \amp=\frac{9}{30}\\ \amp=\frac{3}{10} \end{aligned} ```]
So [`\frac{5}{6}y-\frac{8}{15}y=\frac{3}{10}y\text{.}`] And together with the third term, the answer is [`\frac{3}{10}y+\frac{2}{3}y^2\text{.}`]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
Section::End();
